The paper deals with 3D facial shape reconstruction using deep neural networks, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of DNNs for end-to-end reconstruction also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a fusion convolutional neural network, which is a technique commonly used in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
